member.name: T:SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints
member.summary: Constraints inform the entity resolver about the capabilities an conditional entity must have on game level. Without any constraints, the conditional entity could be anything on game level. Ð¡onstraints allow to resolve conditional entity to entity on game level that is the fittest to the host method.

member.name: F:SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints.CanBeTaken
member.summary: Entity on game level can be taken by NPC's hands. For example, entities which are held by another NPC will be ignored.

member.name: F:SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints.OnlyVisible
member.summary: Entity on game level should be visible for the NPC. Invisible entities will be ignored.

member.name: F:SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints.OnlyInvisible
member.summary: Entity on game level should not be visible for the NPC. Visible entities will be ignored.

member.name: F:SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints.Nearest
member.summary: The nearest entity on game level will be preferred.

member.name: M:SymOntoClay.Core.IEntity.SpecifyOnce(SymOntoClay.Core.EntityConstraints[])

member.param: Array of constraints.

member.name: M:SymOntoClay.Core.IEntity.SpecifyOnce(SymOntoClay.Core.IStorage)
member.summary: Sets backpack storage that will be used during resolving. It allows to resolve entity in way which is fit for the host-method. This backpack storage will be used once. Next resolving will not use this backpack storage.
member.param: Backpack storage

member.name: M:SymOntoClay.Core.IEntity.ResolveIfNeeds
